-1.1,\nconfirming their well-established old age. The preliminary investigation of the\nH-band luminosity evolution of 63 BCGs provides for the first time direct\nobservational indications that the most massive cluster galaxies have doubled\ntheir stellar mass since z~1.5. The finding that BCGs were assembled in the\nlast 9Gyr is now in qualitative agreement with the latest simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Jun 2008 20:32:37 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-06-06"}
