tightly\nconstrain its orbital parameters. The data are inconsistent with a radial\norbit, and imply inner and outer turning radii of r_i ~ 300 kpc and r_o > 8.8\nMpc, indicating that M86 is, at best, only weakly bound to the Virgo cluster.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 4 Jun 2008 21:11:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
